spans.text: O ! formed by nature , and refined by art , With charms
O ! formed by nature , and refined by art , With charms
while thy summers are my theme
Fancy has figured out our calm retreat
the night , 'Midst gardens here my humble pile shall rise
shall warble cross the gloomy grove
lure the trout with well-dissembled flies
lure the trout with well-dissembled flies
lure the trout with well-dissembled flies
thy twinkling eyes oppressed , Soft whispering
let me warn my love to rest
a daughter's shame ; This coxcomb's ribbon cost him half his land , And oaks , unnumbered , bought that fool a wand
Mean while , in hope a guiltless country swain , My reed with warblings
